We can create instances of each of the two extremely rigid variants by using the `::` syntax:

```rust
let four = IpAddrKind::V4;
let six = IpAddrKind::V6;
```

Here is where Rust Enums crush other languages: You can seamlessly attach internal data directly to each variant!

```rust
enum IpAddr {
    V4(u8, u8, u8, u8),
    V6(String),
}

let home = IpAddr::V4(127, 0, 0, 1);
let loopback = IpAddr::V6(String::from("::1"));
```
